Hi , My name was Doc Jake, I served with First Shore Party Battalion, First marine Division.  My tour of duty was Feb 4 1968 to Feb 9 1969.  I spent a good bit of time in the bush.  After losing two VERY GOOD Friends, I made it a practice not to remember any bodies name.  I wish I didn't do that because Today I can remember No Ones name that I served with, Marines or Corpsmen.  I am looking for anyone who served at that time.  I'm not sure this is the right forum for this but this is the first time I've done this.  Well if anything maybe this will help inside. It seems that the only time I can really talk about my expieriences is when I've been drinking.  I wish you all a happy new year.<br>
                            <br>

<p><code>-- pajakubc@iserv.net  (Rich Jakubczak, Doc Jake) </code><p>


